1 NAME John /James/
2 GIVN John
2 SURN James
2 _MARNM James
1 SEX M
1 BIRT
2 DATE 30 MAY 1937
1 NOTE Bio notes: Grew up in Upper Darby. Very close with sister. Went to the movies together. 
2 CONT 
2 CONT Helped dad with resturant on saturdays. would ride into philly together. didn't know him that well. He worked a lot.
2 CONT 
2 CONT Mother was very strict. Had to do everything her way. 
2 CONT 
2 CONT Had a close childhood friend named Billy Cook, Michael McHale - neighborhood people. Used to walk to school together. 
2 CONT 
2 CONT In HS, would take the bus to school in West Philly. You'd have tokens/reduced fair. West Catholic High School. Then went to Villanova.
2 CONT 
2 CONT Got a "fellowship" to Nova. Became friends with father Nangioni (sp. ?). Offered John a fellowship for librarian. Went to graduate school for library, although it wasn't acredited. So he went to Drexel instead. 
2 CONT 
2 CONT He liked the people and the work of librarians. Sometimes even today (at age 88) he helps out with the library at the retirement home - at the Quadrangle. 
2 CONT 
2 CONT People would ask him specific facts, and he would know answers to various topics. People would come to him for help with research papers.
2 CONT 
2 CONT Met Kathleen at a marriage encounter group at the Parish. First friday of every month. They had dancing. Got to meet people with your religion. 
2 CONT 
2 CONT Wanted to meet people. early 20s. Had gone to a couple of these before. 
2 CONT 
2 CONT Thought Kathleen was beautiful, wonderful personality, got along with everybody.
2 CONT 
2 CONT Eugene Garfield was publishing a reference book called the "Science Citation Index" - said there's an opening for the managing editor. The only downside was that it was far. So he would take the "PTC" (or Septa) to 49th street. Worked there for 2 years. Managed 100+ people. They had to keypunch everything into these ID cards. then another group would do site verification where they would check they key punchers. Edward Write wasn't very good. But if it passed through that, it would go through the publication.
2 CONT 
2 CONT Didn't want to take the bus anymore so quit. 
2 CONT 
2 CONT Married Kathleen when he was 30.
2 CONT 
2 CONT Started playing the piano at 8 years old. Could walk to his piano teacher's house. Miss Craig. Asked to learn because he liked piano. Played Oregon at St. Allow's Church. Warsaw Concerto was his favorite piece. 22 pages. 
2 CONT 
2 CONT In HS, hard to play piano because of the transportation.
2 CONT 
2 CONT Wedding was very formal, it was a mass. Old latin hyms. Father Rongioni said the mass. Went to Bermuda. Lot of beach days. 
2 CONT 
2 CONT Bought house in Upper Darby and moved in with Kathleen right after the honeymoon
2 CONT 
2 CONT Continued the marriage encounter, but fizzled out after children. 
2 CONT 
2 CONT Loved parenting. Very good at following routine and structure. 
2 CONT 
2 CONT At this point, he worked for Wyatt Labs. Formula division - got a bunch of free instant formula from them. 
2 CONT 
2 CONT In charge of the library community. 4 libraries at Wyatt labs - Radnor, Philly, Bluebell, Willowgrove. 
2 CONT 
2 CONT IST (institute of scientific information) -> Wyath for 40 years
2 CONT 
2 CONT Travelled a lot. Greece was his favorite vacation. 
2 CONT 
2 CONT Kathleen decided that the house was too big so they decided to downsize.
2 CONT 
2 CONT Liked it at the Benson House.
2 CONT 
2 CONT 
2 CONT 
2 CONT Life lessons: be very visible, be outgoing
