1 NAME Thomas /Jacob Shryock/
2 GIVN Thomas
2 SURN Jacob Shryock
2 _MARNM Jacob Shryock
1 SEX M
1 BIRT
2 DATE 27 FEB 1851
2 PLAC Baltimore, Md.
1 DEAT Y
1 OCCU Wholesale Lumber Merchant
1 NOTE Bio notes: Masonic:
2 CONT - Born February 27th. 1851, in Baltimore, Md.
2 CONT - Made a Mason in 1875, in Waverly Lodge, #152
2 CONT - Master of the Lodge in 1876
2 CONT - Elected Junior Grand Warden in 1878
2 CONT - Elected Senior Grand Warden in 1882
2 CONT - Elected Deputy Grand Master in 1884
2 CONT - Elected Grand Master of Masons in 1885
2 CONT Chapter:
2 CONT - Past High Priest
2 CONT - Past Grand Treasurer Grand Chapter of Maryland
2 CONT - Past Thrice Illustrious Master
2 CONT - Past Royal & Select Master
2 CONT - Past Grand Master Grand Council Royal & Select Master
2 CONT Knights Templar:
2 CONT - Eminent Commander Beauseany Commander, #8
2 CONT - Past Grand Commander of Knights Templar
2 CONT Scottish Rite:
2 CONT - 33º Ancient & Accepted Scottish Rite in 1888
2 CONT - Active Member Supreme Council Southern Jurisdiction
2 CONT - Sovereign Grand Inspector General for Maryland
2 CONT Sociatas Rosicruciana:
2 CONT - Supreme Grand Magus of the United States
2 CONT Honorary:
2 CONT - Honorary Past Grand Master of Egypt
2 CONT - Honorary member of large number of lodges in Europe
2 CONT Political
2 CONT - Appointed on Staff of Henry Lloyd, Governor of Maryland
2 CONT - Elected Treasurer of State of Maryland by Legislator, being the only Republican State Treasurer Maryland ever had
2 CONT -Appointed Police Commissioner of Baltimore City by a Democratic Governor, to assist in taking the Department out of politics
