1 NOTE Bio notes: Henry Shryock was an officer in the Revolutionary War. He was Lieutenant Colonel of the Sixth Battalion, under Colonel Otho Holland Williams. See McSherry's History of Maryland; page 382, Appendix B, and page 387, Appendix C.
2 CONT See--"Historical Register of      the Officers of the Continental Army during the Revolutionary Apr. 1775 to Dec 1783." by T.B. Heitman of the
2 CONT War Department, as follows: ---
2 CONT "Shryock, Henry, (Md.) Lieut.  Colonel 1st Maryland Battalion of the Flying Camp June to Dec 1776. Lieut.  Colonel 6th. Maryland, Dec. 10 1776 to Apr. 17th. 1777."
2 CONT There is in the possession of my father, General Thomas Jacob Shryock, the original letter of Henry Shryock to the Colonial Council, asknowledging his commission as Lieutenant Colonel of the 1st. Flying Camp. Also, a Treasury warrant for supplies taken by him for his troops.
2 CONT Maryland Convention, April 28th. 1788. Signer of the Ratification of the Constitution of the United States of America, and as a delegate to the Maryland Convention. See McSherry's History of Maryland, page 402. Also, Scharf's History; Vol. 2, page 194. S.R.H.Reg.Gen.
